 you know what's going on, God. It doesn't seem like you care, you're acting. Through our eyes, perhaps it seems random, arbitrary, somewhat chaotic, what happens in this world. And yet, we need to remember the Word of God and what He says. Everything is ordained of God from eternity. And He brings it about in time according to His providence. As we heard about that again this morning. Those troubles and afflictions that come upon us even at the hand of men, even at the hand of men, they seem so meaningless, sometimes random, but they're all governed by the sovereign God of heaven and earth. And that means for the people of God that there is a guarantee confirmed by His Word that He will work all things together for our good. And we know that Jesus Christ as Mediator King, as the Governor of the nations, has been given power and authority to govern here in this way over all creation for our good, for the sake of the church, Ephesians 1. Remember back in Isaiah 9 about His government. Unto us a child is born. Unto us a son is given. And the government shall be upon His shoulder. And His name shall be called Wonderful Counselor, the Mighty God, the Everlasting Father, the Prince of Peace. Of the increase of His government and peace, there shall be no end upon the throne of David and upon His kingdom to order it and to establish it with judgment and with justice from henceforth even forever. The zeal of the Lord of Hosts will perform this. And so Jesus as our Mediator King, the Governor of the nations, He executes the Father's will we heard this morning for the good of His people. And so here, what appears to men to be random or chaotic or arbitrary is the providence of the all-wise God in Jesus Christ who is the Governor of the nations. Do you understand that? That nothing, absolutely nothing comes upon us by chance. It's not just fate. It's not just something that happens on a whim. Or according to the will of man. It is all ordained by Jehovah, the living and true G