at evil amongst the nations. But this coming together by them is vanity, the Lord says here. And the second thing that they do is continue in idolatry. Verse 7, So the carpenter encouraged the goldsmith, and he that smootheth with the hammer, him that smote the anvil, saying, it is ready for the soldering, and he fastened it with nails that it should not be moved. They're working together. They're coming together, these nations. Here in verse 7, there's different types of craftsmen. And the illustration is speaking of these are the nations, the different nations coming together. They have a different part they can do. But it shows to us in this illustration their idolatries coming together, that they work together. The carpenter, he makes the basic structure. The goldsmith and the metalworker, they overlay it with gold and hammer it into place. And then they need some soldering to fasten it all together. And then someone nails it to the wall to fix it in place. And they coming together doing this to determine that'll help against this great power of Cyrus, which is in the background, of course, we know is the Lord, verse 4. It's the Lord who's sending Cyrus. And so what the nations are coming together and doing is like, well, we just need to come together and get better at idolatry. That's what we need to do. Let's come together. Let's pull our idolatry, our various gods, our false gods, together into some new idols or new idol. And if you know your history in the world, this also happens a lot. There is a constant folly in the heart of man without saving grace. In every crisis, he comes up with the same predictable act of unbelief. The form of it varies, but it's really much more of the same, idolatry. And so Cyrus is coming. We'll stand together. We'll make some new idols. All is going to be well. Men continue to walk in darkness without the renewing work of the Holy Spirit who alone is able to bring them and make them willing to believe the truth and trust in the