riend forever? James 2. And the Scripture was fulfilled which says, Abraham believed God and it was imputed unto him for righteousness, and he was called the friend of God. What is it to be the friend of God? It is to be at peace with God. To be forgiven and accepted in Christ Jesus. To be in the bond of the everlasting covenant. Genesis 18, the Lord said, Shall I hide from Abraham that thing which I do, seeing that Abraham shall surely become a great and mighty nation and all the nations of the earth shall be blessed in him? The Lord said, Shall I hide from Abraham what I do? The answer there, No. Abraham is his friend. And so he tells Abraham what he will do. He shows Abraham his counsel and purpose just as he does thankfully to each of us here. Psalm 25. It says, The secret of the Lord is with them that fear Him, and He will show them His covenant. That word secret in Psalm 25 has the idea of confiding friendship or confiding in your friend. And we confide our secrets in our friends and those near us. Here it is the Lord, He opens His truth to His friends. John 15, You are My friends, if you do whatsoever I command you. Henceforth I call you not servants, for the servant knoweth not what his Lord doeth, but I have called you friends. For all things that I have heard of My Father I have made known unto you. You have not chosen Me, but I have chosen you and ordained you that you should go and bring forth fruit and that your fruit should remain that whatsoever you so ask of the Father in My name He may give it you. Jesus is saying, You are all My friends because the Father has given you to Me. He's teaching them the purpose of the Father in which He is confiding in His friend not that the Lord needs to do that in the way that we do when we confide in someone, but He's opening up His counsel to His friends so that they can know. They can have knowledge of the truth, of the good news of the Gospel, and even what is to come so that they would be prepared for it. That's what a friend will do. They'll tell you the truth. That's what the Lord does with us as people. And so the people of God have the Word of God. They've been given grace to begin to understand it. And so they do understand what the world does not understand. Now, the Lord has not revealed everything to us, but the Scriptures tell us all that we need to know. And as God's people search the Scriptures, the Lord gives understanding by His grace and Spirit so that His people increase in their understanding of the Word of God. And though our understanding is finite, it's limited, yet the people of God live in, like we heard last Lord's Day, in a different world in the sense compared to the ungodly who believe all their lives and they live in this fantasy world. The ungodly do not understand. They may have a mass of individual facts that are out there in the world, but really to them, it's no meaning. It has no meaning. No true meaning. The connections aren't there. But the weakest believer, the little ones, the weakest believer understands because he knows the God of Heaven and receives the truth. He has an understanding, not complete understanding, but understanding nonetheless, a beginning of understanding that even the wise and mighty of the world, the intelligent, the geniuses of the world who know not God, who are fools, that they don't have. And so the ungodly, they talk as if they know, but they don't really know. They don't know why they're here. They don't want to know why they're here. They don't know where they're going and yet they put on a show. They put on a pretense. Ungodly people are pretending all the time that they have some idea of what's really happening in this world. And they have no idea what's happening in this world because they don't believe the truth. They've rejected it. They've suppressed that knowledge. The Word of the Lord is not in them, but the people of God know. And so when Cyrus comes, the Lord's instrument, He's speaking to His people