righteous, but that there is an instrument being used by the Lord bringing this man from the east, and he will be the instrument of the Lord's righteousness. Not necessarily his righteousness, it is the Lord's righteousness and him being used as an instrument of the Lord. \n\nFrom this we would believe this refers to Cyrus the king of the Medes and Persians. And so here is another early reference to even before the Babylonian exile, even before Cyrus is alive. Another example of this in the book of Isaiah. In Isaiah we've seen this before. There have been many things that have been introduced little by little. Even through the book of Isaiah, it's progressively revealed, just like the covenants are progressively revealed throughout all the Scriptures. So, there are certain things in Isaiah, the book itself that's introduced and revealed to us little by little with general comments, beginning with general comments with no names, to then later revealing more. \n\nWe heard early on about how Assyria, they knew about Assyria at the time, but they were told it's not going to be Assyria that takes you captive. They will not defeat you. But there is another nation who will take you into captivity, but we didn't know the nation's name yet. We knew, of course, because we're looking at all the Scriptures, but they didn't know yet. And then just recently we read how the Lord revealed it was Babylon who was going to do this. Well, Babylon's not even a great nation yet. And at the time of the first revealing of the nation's going to take you into captivity, Babylon wasn't even close to being known among the people. So here it is the same with the identity of Cyrus. In Isaiah 45 it says this, Thus saith the Lord to His anointed, to Cyrus, whose right hand I have holden to subdue nations before him, and I will loose the loins of kings to open before him the two leaved gates, and the gates shall not be shut. I will go before thee and make the crooked places straight. I will break i