, calling the generations from the beginning even I the Lord, the first and with the last, I am He. \n\nSo long before Cyrus was even around, the Lord's revealing this to His people of Judah. This is again before the Babylonian exile even started. Before Babylon is itself a world power called the world power later in the Scriptures. You see, the Lord did this. He says, I have this purpose fixed so much so that it is for Me, for the Lord. It is already history. It is that certain that it's already accomplished. That you will go into exile. Cyrus, My servant, will deliver you. He is the One who calls the generations into existence. He is the eternal God. He is the first and the last. He's always been, He always will be. \n\nAnd He governs everything in every generation. And you remember this is the title given as well to the Lord Jesus, Revelation 1, saying, I am Alpha and Omega, the first and the last. In Revelation 22, beginning of Revelation, and end of Revelation. The same thing, I am Alpha and Omega, the beginning and the end, the first and the last. Because the Lord Jesus is Jehovah, the second person of the one Godhead, He is called the beginning and the end. And here is the Lord declaring that He has ordained the end from the beginning. \n\nThat the whole history of man and his people, all generations, is ordained from before the foundation of the world, much similar to what we heard this morning. And that, of course, includes Judas' captivity in Babylon. It includes Cyrus' conquering Babylon as a means of deliverance and sending them back to Jerusalem. That this was ordained of God from eternity. Friends, if those things are true, we also know, yes, they are true. We also know everything else that occurs in this world is also ordained of God from all eternity. And from this, we can draw comfort. Just like we heard this morning, we draw comfort from these things. \n\nComfort from a God who is in complete control. And comfort. But it's a comfort that's only gra