 That nothing, absolutely nothing comes upon us by chance. It's not just fate. It's not just something that happens on a whim. Or according to the will of man. It is all ordained by Jehovah, the living and true God, and governed through Jesus Christ as our Mediator and King, working to save all of His elect in this world and so for the good of the church. Now would the people of God desire not to be afflicted? Yeah, of course. Would the people of Judah desire not to go into the Babylonian captivity? Of course they would not want to go into the Babylonian captivity. They would prefer not to go. And yet it was ordained by the Lord our God and He was glorified in it and brought this upon His people for their good, for the remnant within Judah, the believing true covenant keepers from amongst the many covenant breakers. He did it for their good. \n\nAnd so it is our duty in similar things to see the hand of the Lord working in all things and let us see His wisdom and grace seeking them out, meditating upon His Word that we would see these things, all things that come upon us even at the hands of the ungodly. And we would see it in accordance with His eternal decrees and good providence for our good, whether the providence seems good or is dark at the time of its coming. We would still see it as God working for our good. And so the governor of the nations is Jesus Christ, and we're thankful that He is in complete control.\n\n### The Nation's Vanity in Coming Together\n\nA third point, the nation's vanity in coming together. Verse 5, the isles saw it and feared. The ends of the earth were afraid, drew near and came. They helped everyone his neighbor, and everyone said to his brother, be of good courage. And so the carpenter encouraged the goldsmith. And he that smootheth with the hammer, him that smote the anvil, saying, it is ready for the soldering, and he fastened it with nails that it should not be moved. This is the reaction of the nations to Cyrus's conquering approach. There are two main things here of their reaction. The first thing that they do knowing Cyrus is going to come up against them is they come together. They join up forces. They make alliances. \n\nIt says, the isles saw it and feared. They were in a panic. Where did they turn? Did they turn to the Lord? No. It says, the ends of the earth were afraid, drew near and came. And what's saying there is that they came together. That's the word used. They came together. They turned to one another. And so verse 6, they helped everyone his neighbor, and everyone said to his brother, be of good courage or be strong. They come together. They try to reassure themselves that they can deal with this Cyrus thing and this great army of his. The wicked today do the same thing in our day. The nations do this today. \n\nAnd it is meaningless unity or what appears to be unity. It's not unity as described by God in the scriptures, but it's the appearance of unity. And it's meaningless. They don't have these nations coming together like the United Nations, the European Union, G8, NATO, all these kind of things. We go on and on. There's many of them today. Many forms they take from various nations so that today whatever comes to these nations, they say, we can handle it. We just need to come together. We need to join together. That's the answer. We need more nations to come together. There's terrorism. There's Russia or whoever the great enemy might be the next day and today. \n\nWe just need to come together and stand together against this evil or that evil, so they call it. But you have to ask yourself, what is evil without God? What is evil without God? The ungodly do not know. They have no true definition of evil because without God, there's no such thing as good and evil. And they don't believe in God. Because God defines what is good. He defines what is evil. What is the living and true God? What He approves of and does is good by definition. It has to be good because He's infinite, eternal, and unchangeable in His goodness. He is good. What He says is good. What He approves of is good. All that contradicts His Word is evil.\n\nAnd so men talk of standing together as if they know what is good and therefore they can combat evil amongst the nations. But this coming together by them is vanity, the Lord says here. And the second thing that they do is continue in idolatry. Verse 7, So the carpenter encouraged the goldsmith, and he that smootheth with the hammer, him that smote the anvil, saying, it is ready for the soldering, and he fastened it with nails that it should not be moved. They're working together. They're coming together, these nations. Here in verse 7, there's different types of craftsmen. And the illustration is speaking of these are the nations, the different nations coming together. They have a different part they can do. But it shows to us in this illustration their idolatries coming together, that they work together. \n\nThe carpenter, he makes the basic structure. The goldsmith and the metalworker, they overlay it with gold and hammer it into place. And then they need some soldering to fasten it all together. And then someone nails it to the wall to fix it in place. And they coming together doing this to determine that'll help against this great power of Cyrus, which is in the background, of course, we know is the Lord, verse 4. It's the Lord who's sending Cyrus. And so what the nations are coming together and doing is like, well, we just need to come together and get better at idolatry. That's what we need to do. Let's come together. Let's pull our idolatry, our various gods, our false gods, together into some new idols or new idol. \n\nAnd if you know your history in the world, this also happens a lot. There is a constant folly in the heart of man without saving grace. In every crisis, he comes up with the same predictable act of unbelief. The form of it varies, but it's really much more of the same, idolatry. And so Cyrus is coming. We'll stand together. We'll make some new idols. All is going to be well. Men continue to walk in darkness without the renewing work of the Holy Spirit who alone is able to bring them and make them willing to believe the truth and trust in the Lord Jesus Christ. They're fearful. They're afraid. But they look to one another. They look to false religion, to their imaginary gods to help them, and not to Jehovah and Jesus Christ. \n\nThe nation's vanity in coming together.\n\n### The Friends of God Need Not Fear\n\nAnd then, fourthly, the friends of God need not fear. The friends of God need not fear. Verse 8, but thou, Israel, art My servant. Jacob, whom I have chosen, the seed of Abraham My friend. Thou whom I have taken from the ends of the earth and called thee from the chief men thereof and said unto thee, Thou art My servant. I have chosen thee and not cast thee away. And verse 10 goes on and says, Fear thou not, for I am with thee. The Lord reveals here that the people of God must be totally different than the nations. They were chosen by the Lord, or the Lord chose Israel as a people to be His bride, the church, and on earth, the visible church, the outward form of the church. But the Lord also chose individuals to be heirs of salvation. \n\nHe had chosen them to be His servant. Verse 8, it says, But thou, Israel, art My servant. Jacob, whom I have chosen. And this divine choice caused Israel to be His servant. It wasn't the other way around. It wasn't the Lord's choice. It wasn't the people's choice that caused them to be the Lord's. It was the Lord's choosing of them that made them to be His servants. Both in the outward sense and the ultimate sense of the actual born-again people of God. And so there is in the sense of the corporate people of God, the Lord chose the corporate people of God. He also chose us individually. And both those senses are here described. God had chosen the heirs of salvation. \n\nAnd He calls them the seed of Abraham as promised in Covenant. My friend. In the Scriptures, Abraham is called a couple of times the friend of God. 2 Chronicles 20, King Jehoshaphat is praying to the Lord. He says, Art not thou our God who didst drive out the inhabitants of this land before thy people Israel and gavest it to the seed of Abraham, thy friend forever? James 2. And the Scripture was fulfilled which says, Abraham believed God and it was imputed unto him for righteousness, and he was called the friend of God. What is it to be the friend of God? It is to be at peace with God. To be forgiven and accepted in Christ Jesus. To be in the bond of the everlasting covenant. \n\nGenesis 18, the Lord said, Shall I hide from Abraham that thing which I do, seeing that Abraham shall surely become a great and mighty nation and all the nations of the earth shall be blessed in him? The Lord said, Shall I hide from Abraham what I do? The answer there, No. Abraham is his friend. And so he tells Abraham what he will do. He shows Abraham his counsel and purpose just as he does thankfully to each of us here. Psalm 25. It says, The secret of the Lord is with them that fear Him, and He will show them His covenant. That word secret in Psalm 25 has the idea of confiding friendship or confiding in your friend. \n\nAnd we confide our secrets in our friends and those near us. Here it is the Lord, He opens His truth to His friends. John 15, You are My friends, if you do whatsoever I command you. Henceforth I call you not servants, for the servant knoweth not what his Lord doeth, but I have called you friends. For all things that I have heard of My Father I have made known unto you. You have not chosen Me, but I have chosen you and ordained you that you should go and bring forth fruit and that your fruit should remain, that whatsoever ye shall ask of the Father in My name He may give it you. Jesus is saying, You are all My friends because the Father has given you to Me. \n\nHe's teaching them the purpose of the Father in which He is confiding in His friend not that the Lord needs to do that in the way that we do when we confide in someone, but He's opening up His counsel to His friends so that they can know. They can have knowledge of the truth, of the good news of the Gospel, and even what is to come so that they would be prepared for it. That's what a friend will do. They'll tell you the truth. That's what the Lord does with us as people. And so the people of God have the Word of God. They've been given grace to begin to understand it. \n\nAnd so they do understand what the world does not understand. Now, the Lord has not revealed everything to us, but the Scriptures tell us all that we need to know. And as God's people search the Scriptures, the Lord gives understanding by His grace and Spirit so that His people increase in their understanding of the Word of God. And though our understanding is finite, it's limited, yet the people of God live in, like we heard last Lord's Day, in a different world in the sense compared to the ungodly who believe all their lives and they live in this fantasy world. The ungodly do not understand. \n\nThey may have a mass of individual facts that are out there in the world, but really to them, it's no meaning. It has no meaning. No true meaning. The connections aren't there. But the weakest believer, the little ones, the weakest believer understands because he knows the God of Heaven and receives the truth. He has an understanding, not complete understanding, but understanding nonetheless, a beginning of understanding that even the wise and mighty of the world, the intelligent, the geniuses of the world who know not God, who are fools, that they don't have. And so the ungodly, they talk as if they know, but they don't really know. They don't know why they're here. They don't want to know why they're here. They don't know where they're going and yet they put on a show. They put on a pretense. \n\nUngodly people are pretending all the time that they have some idea of what's really happening in this world. And they have no idea what's happening in this world because they don't believe the truth. They've rejected it. They've suppressed that knowledge. The Word of the Lord is not in them, but the people of God know. And so when Cyrus comes, the Lord's instrument, He's speaking to His people Judah. When Cyrus comes with all His armies and the nations panic and come together and make their idols, the Lord says, fear not. Fear not, for the Lord will work Cyrus for your good. \n\nAnd He'll deliver you from Babylon. He will govern Cyrus and every one of His soldiers for the good of His church and His people. And so it says in verse 9, Thou whom I have taken from the ends of the earth and called Thee from the chief men thereof and said unto Thee, Thou art My servant. I have chosen Thee and not cast Thee away. The regathering of a scattered people under the oppression of the mighty from captivity in Babylon. And there may be also a thought here of looking beyond to the engathering of the elect of God from among the nations and the Gentiles. But verse 10, He says, fear not. I have called Thee. Thou art My servant. Verse 9, The Lord will preserve His people a seed to serve Him in each generation. \n\nAnd we know the promises. The mercy of the Lord is everlasting to everlasting upon them that fear Him and His righteousness unto children's children such as keep His covenant. The covenant made with Abraham would stand to a thousand generations. Each generation still stands today. And the elect of God enabled to keep the covenant through faith in the coming Savior at that time. God would be their God in each generation. So they need not be afraid because like Abraham, they're friends of God. They have the knowledge of God in Christ Jesus. They know that He governs all things for their good as was already prophesied in Isaiah 9. They know. \n\nTheir life, they know, is hidden with God in Christ. And they, as we heard this morning, will be preserved, kept. Not one of His little ones will perish. Colossians 3, when Christ who is our life shall appear, then shall ye also appear with Him in glory. So the blessedness of the people of God is so great to have this God as our God and Jesus Christ to be an heir of God. Joint heirs with Christ to know that you have been chosen in Christ before the foundation of the world. To know that you've been born from above by the Holy Spirit and enabled by His grace to embrace the promises of mercy in Christ Jesus found in the Gospel. To know that the God who made the heavens, that He and His Son is governing all things in our interest for our sake. \n\nAnd by the Holy Spirit has granted us to know these things and understand these things. And so here He exhorts you be not like the nations. Be not like the world that do not believe in fear. Fear not with their fear. They have reason to be afraid. They have reason to be afraid of every falling leaf in the fall, every droplet of rain in the spring. They have reason to be afraid of these things. Everything that contains care and the grounds of fear for the ungodly. But the people of God, those who know their God, who trust in Christ, they can be strong by turning to Him, waiting upon Him and knowing that He will renew their strength. \n\nAnd so we're called as we were last Lord's Day to fix our hearts to trust in the Lord, confident in Him and His Word, His promises, hope in His promises, and let not your heart be troubled. Now, neither let your heart be afraid, but turn to the Lord and put your confidence in Him. He says, Fear thou not for I am with thee. Be not dismayed for I am thy God. I will strengthen thee. Yea, I will help thee. I will uphold thee with my right hand of my righteousness. And so, put your confidence in the Lord and turn to Him. \n\n### Closing Prayer\n\nLet's pray. Gracious Father, thankful for Your almighty power and strength, Your hand of providence that is good to us, Your people, Your grace and Your Holy Spirit and Your mercy as You work in us by Your Spirit, grace upon grace. Cause us not to fear, but hope and trust and grant us greater understanding of the truth in Your Word. Keep us from every false way and complaining and grumbling as well, questioning You as if You couldn't see, as if You don't know that You're not going to act. We know that You will act as You've given all authority in heaven and on earth to the Lord Jesus Christ, our Mediator and King, the Governor of the nations, and He rules over all, even now, for the sake of the church. \n\nAnd as we put our confidence and our hope, we pray in Jesus' name. Amen."
